<doc id="163013" wikidata="Q6919396" url="?curid=163013" title="Mount Analogue (disambiguation)">
<text>Mount Analogue (French: &quot;Le Mont Analogue&quot;) is a novel by René Daumal, posthumously published in 1952 in French and 1959 in English.

Mount Analogue may also refer to:
* Mount Analogue (Antarctica), a mountain
* &quot;Mount Analogue&quot; (album)
* &quot;Mount Analogue&quot;, a song by Idlewild from the album &quot;Interview Music&quot;</text><links>
<link wikidata="Q1773497" start="0" end="14" title="Mount Analogue" label="Mount Analogue"/>
